Diagnosis. Externally, the species differs from its closest relative, 
<taxonomicName id="B18F1DF7FFBF481F5844FAE3FB617A07" authorityName="Inoue" authorityYear="1965" box="[1045,1192,1322,1348]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nipponasura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinea">
<emphasis id="44FBBA66FFBF481F5844FAE3FB617A07" box="[1045,1192,1322,1348]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="370">S. sanguinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by presence of crosslines on forewings and darker hindwings of both sexes. In the male genitalia, 
<taxonomicName id="B18F1DF7FFBF481F5CFFFAA3FEF97AC7" box="[174,304,1386,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sesapa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inscripta">
<emphasis id="44FBBA66FFBF481F5CFFFAA3FEF97AC7" box="[174,304,1386,1412]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="370">S. inscripta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="B18F1DF7FFBF481F5D82FAA3FDAF7AC7" authorityName="Inoue" authorityYear="1965" box="[467,614,1386,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nipponasura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinea">
<emphasis id="44FBBA66FFBF481F5D82FAA3FDAF7AC7" box="[467,614,1386,1412]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="370">S. sanguinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the narrower uncus, the slightly smaller medial costal process, the shorter apical membranous lobe of valva, the shorter, C-like curved distal saccular process, the larger aedeagus (in comparison with the genital capsule), and presence of only two clusters of spines in the vesica (whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="B18F1DF7FFBF481F5F7BFA03FC717AA7" authorityName="Inoue" authorityYear="1965" box="[810,952,1482,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nipponasura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinea">
<emphasis id="44FBBA66FFBF481F5F7BFA03FC717AA7" box="[810,952,1482,1508]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="370">S. sanguinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there is one more small bunch-like cluster). In the female genitalia, 
<taxonomicName id="B18F1DF7FFBF481F5EEEFA23FC8B7947" box="[703,834,1514,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sesapa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inscripta">
<emphasis id="44FBBA66FFBF481F5EEEFA23FC8B7947" box="[703,834,1514,1540]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="370">S. inscripta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="B18F1DF7FFBF481F5FB7FA23FBB17947" authorityName="Inoue" authorityYear="1965" box="[998,1144,1514,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nipponasura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinea">
<emphasis id="44FBBA66FFBF481F5FB7FA23FBB17947" box="[998,1144,1514,1540]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="370">S. sanguinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shorter apophyses anteriores, the narrower antevaginal plate, the narrower ductus bursae, the narrower appendix bursae, and the weaker spines in the posterior section of corpus bursae.
</paragraph>
